ally low\nX-ray luminosities. We find that about half of the population of\noptically-selected type 2 quasars are likely to be Compton-thick. We also find\nno evidence that the amount of X-ray obscuration depends on the AGN luminosity\n(over a range of more than three orders-of-magnitude in luminosity).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Apr 2012 21:23:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 29 Aug 2013 06:47:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
