{"id":"1205.0081","submitter":"Amarendra Kumar Sarma Dr.","authors":"Parvendra Kumar and Amarendra K. Sarma","title":"Optical dipole force on ladder-like three-level atomic systems driven by\n  chirped few-cycle-pulse laser fields","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Physical Review A 86, 053414 (2012)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.86.053414","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.optics physics.atom-ph quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We report a study on the optical dipole force in a ladder like three level\natomic systems in the context of coherent population transfer with the chirped\nfew-cycle-pulse laser fields. The phenomenon of coherent population transfer is\ninvestigated by numerically solving the appropriate density matrix equations\nbeyond the rotating wave approximation. On the other hand, optical dipole force\nis calculated by numerically solving the force equation and density matrix\nequations self-consistently. By analysing the centre-of-mass motion, it is\nshown that the optical dipole force with chirped pulses may be used for\nfocusing and defocusing of atoms in an atomic beam similar to the near or\nnon-resonant optical dipole force. Moreover, the robustness of the population\ntransfer against the variation of the pulse parameters and the effect of the\nvariation of the Rabi frequencies and the chirp rates on the optical dipole\nforce are also investigated. The proposed scheme may open new perspectives in\nthe focusing and de-focusing of atoms and molecules in an atomic beam, since\nthis scheme mitigates the demand for the generation of transform-limited pulse\nlaser fields at arbitrary frequencies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 May 2012 04:07:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 26 Jun 2012 17:52:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-12-20"}
